726107f-a.title: Queens: Atlantic Avenue - 75th Street
726107f-a.text:
(1)
Atlantic Avenue, east from 75th Street, seen from the
avenue's north lane. Behind the wooden fence is the main
line of the Long Island Railroad. In the lft background
is the wooden bridge over which runs Rockaway Boulevard.
P. L. Sperr  July 27, 1930
NO REPRODUCTIONS
(2)
Atlantic Avenue, looking east from 78th Street and showing
a closer view of the Rockaway Boulevard bridge.
P. L. Sperr  July 27, 1930
NO REPRODUCTIDNS
